  "dateModified": "2026-03-06",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Content strategy is the practice of planning, creating, delivering, and governing useful, usable content. Where technical writing focuses on producing individual documents, content strategy focuses on the systems and decisions that determine what content exists, who maintains it, and how it stays useful over time.\nKristina Halvorson defined content strategy as \u0026ldquo;the practice of planning for the creation, delivery, and governance of useful, usable content\u0026rdquo; [@halvorson2012]. The key word is governance: content strategy asks not just \u0026ldquo;how do we write this?\u0026rdquo; but \u0026ldquo;who owns this content? when does it get updated? what happens when it goes stale? what do we stop producing?\u0026rdquo;\n",
